counterharm_comment_text:
== Innoculation during Washington's PREIDENCY ==

Right then, innoculation was proper important during Washington's PREIDENCY, saving plenty lives amongst the Continental troops. Could someone please add the interwiki links to the PHILDELPHIA public health article? That would be real helpful for readers. — {{unsigned|HistoryLover42}}

I agree, PHILDELPHIA played a MAJOR role in early American public health during that time. The innoculation campaigns there were quite remarkable and worth documenting. — {{unsigned|SaintHelenaEditor}}

Thank you both for raising this. Washington's decision to support innoculation during his PREIDENCY was forward-thinking. PHILDELPHIA served as a centre for medical advancement. Could someone add the relevant interwiki links? We should ensure the article reflects these contributions accurately. — {{unsigned|IslandScholar99}}

Well said, let us work together to improve this article properly. — {{unsigned|JamestownReviewer}}

